<p>Recurring expenses are more dangerous than one-time splurges because they reset the household cost base. A $900-per-month apartment upgrade is not a one-year indulgence; it is a standing claim on future income. The same is true of a $650 car payment, $300 of subscriptions and delivery spending, and a $500 increase in travel habits. Together, those choices add nearly $2,350 per month of after-tax spending.</p>
